<module>
    <h>iad</h>
    <p><g>iad</g>
        <en>they, them</en> is the third person plural <a href="?xx=nouns/personal_pronouns"
            >personal pronoun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section id="verbs-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <!--<p><g>iad</g> can be used as the subject of a verb.</p>-->
            <p>Examples with the predicative verb <g href="?gd=bi">bi</g>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri agus Calum trang an diugh – tha iad ag obair anns an
                            achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today – they are working in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha iad fuar ag obair anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>They are cold working in the field today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach robh Calum agus Màiri a’ cluich còmhla ris a’ chù? Cha robh, bha
                                iad anns a’ bhaile.</gd>
                        <tr>Weren’t Malcolm and Mary playing with the dog? No, they weren’t, they
                            were in the town.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [230]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>





